&lt;p&gt;This role will require a qualified individual to work onsite three (3) days per week out of our New York City office.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and cultivate relationships with existing and prospective clients to drive revenue growth and ensure retention and expansion with clientele&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supervise members of the Customer Success team&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Successfully manage book of business with&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;minimal involvement from senior management&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities for upselling, cross-selling, and pitching new business ideas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enhance the SaaS customer experience across onboarding, support and account management stages&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead projects and campaigns involving multiple stakeholders, ensuring prompt and efficient turnaround of deliverables&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist Sales team by providing support for proposals and new business initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities for upselling, cross-selling, and pitching new business ideas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and improve customer success KPIs to ensure scalability of processes and frameworks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to and lead strategic discussions with both clients and Constellation leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
